  "prompt": "Does x = 2x, as the limit of x approaches infinity? Why?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) The equation x = 2x means x - 2x = 0\n\n2) Rearranging this, we get -x = 0\n\n3) Solving this, x = 0\n\n4) However, this is specifically true at x = 0, not as x approaches infinity.\n\n5) As x approaches infinity, x is not equal to 2x.\n\n   For example:\n   - If x = 10, 2x = 20\n   - If x = 1000, 2x = 2000\n   - If x = 1,000,000, 2x = 2,000,000\n\n6) In fact, as x approaches infinity, 2x will always be twice x.\n\nTherefore, x = 2x is NOT true as x approaches infinity.\n\nThe answer is NO, x does not equal 2x as x approaches infinity.",
